snippet.title: Two Qantas flights return to Sydney after engineering issues
snippet.content:
Qantas flight to Dallas returns to Sydney after engineering issues.
Share
TWO Qantas flights are returning to Sydney with "engineering issues". Seven News reports Qantas flight A380 QF7 was dumping fuel off the coast. It departed Sydney for Dallas/Fortworth about 1.40pm. There are also report Qantas flight QF63, from Sydney to Johannesburg, has also returned to Sydney. News.com.au has contacted Qantas for comment. More to come.
